<TITLE> University admissions to be streamlined </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 9 (bdnews24.com)--The education ministry has taken steps to simplify the procedure of admission to public universities, an official statement claimed Tuesday. The statement, issued after a meeting of top university officials, said the vice chancellors would work towards integrating the admission process, which would be based on categories such as general, agriculture, medical, science and technology. "An integrated admission system has been planned," adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman, who chaired the meeting, told reporters. The adviser also mentioned that the University Grants Commission (UGC) was drafting a guideline to stop sexual harassment on campuses. Dhaka and Jahangirnagar Universities were working on their own guidelines in this matter, the adviser said. The UGC chairman, 29 VCs and senior ministry officials were present.
